#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/rust-specific/naming.md:22
msgid "End closure variables with `_fn` (`closure-fn-suffix`)"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/rust-specific/naming.md:24
msgid ""
"Variables holding closures or function pointers must signal they are "
"callable by ending with `_fn`. Treating a closure variable as if it were a "
"data object misleads readers."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/rust-specific/naming.md:30
msgid "// Good — clearly a callable\n"
msgstr ""

